name: Chet Holmgren
summary: Oklahoma City Thunder rookie standout Chet Holmgren will miss a significant amount of time due to a fractured hip. Initial reports from Forbes suggest he will be sidelined for multiple months, while official updates from the team and NBA sources indicate he will be out for at least 8-10 weeks. The injury occurred during a fall in a recent game against the Golden State Warriors. The specific nature of the injury is an iliac wing fracture in his pelvis, which is a serious injury that requires a lengthy recovery period. This development is a major setback for the Thunder, who had high hopes for Holmgren this season. His absence will force the team to adjust its frontcourt rotation, leaving questions about how they will fill his place.
